<paragraph blockId="14.[151,737,871,930]" box="[151,300,906,930]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,252,906,930]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–11" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1692,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-92@7.[151,1436,193,1644]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6–11. Adults of Scaeosopha spp. 6, S. percnaula Meyrick, lectotype ♂, Assam, India; 7, S. percnaula Meyrick (= S. stagnigera Meyrick syn. nov., lectotype ♂, Bombay, India); 8, S. sinevi Ponomarenko et Park, ♂, Hong Kong, China; 9, S. betrokensis sp. nov., holotype ♂, Betroka, Madagascar; 10, S. erecta sp. nov., holotype ♂, Hainan, China; 11, S. hongkongensis sp. nov., holotype ♂, Hong Kong, China." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs. 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[264,293,906,930]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–38" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1529,1552]" captionTargetBox="[250,1304,222,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-198@15.[226,1360,193,1508]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 35–38. Male genitalia of Scaeosopha spp. 35, S. hongkongensis sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide no. ZZW08172; 36, S. minuta sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide no. ZZWGW001; 37, S. nullivalvella sp. nov., holotype, BMNH Microlep. slide no. 31013; 38, S. sabahensis sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide no. ZZWGW003." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">35</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,978,1867]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,296,978,1003]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[389,474,978,1002]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–11" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1692,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-92@7.[151,1436,193,1644]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6–11. Adults of Scaeosopha spp. 6, S. percnaula Meyrick, lectotype ♂, Assam, India; 7, S. percnaula Meyrick (= S. stagnigera Meyrick syn. nov., lectotype ♂, Bombay, India); 8, S. sinevi Ponomarenko et Park, ♂, Hong Kong, China; 9, S. betrokensis sp. nov., holotype ♂, Betroka, Madagascar; 10, S. erecta sp. nov., holotype ♂, Hainan, China; 11, S. hongkongensis sp. nov., holotype ♂, Hong Kong, China." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
): Wingspan 13.0 mm. Head with frons grayish-white, vertex with anteriorly tufted brown scales. Antenna with scape yellow except basal half black dorsally, flagellum deep leaden with pale annuli. Labial palpus with second segment grayish-white, third segment deep leaden. Thorax deep-yellow. Tegula with basal half black, distal half yellow. Forewing with ground color yellow, covered with dense dark-brown scales; four black spots along costal margin, elliptical black spot at middle of cell on anterior margin, irregular black spots at end of cell and at middle of fold, arrowhead-shaped black patch near apex; a series of black dots running from distal part of costal margin along termen to tornus; cilia grayish-brown except pale-yellow in distal half. Hindwing and cilia grayish brown. Legs grayish-yellow except fore leg deep-gray.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,978,1867]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[381,467,1266,1290]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–38" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1529,1552]" captionTargetBox="[250,1304,222,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-198@15.[226,1360,193,1508]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 35–38. Male genitalia of Scaeosopha spp. 35, S. hongkongensis sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide no. ZZW08172; 36, S. minuta sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide no. ZZWGW001; 37, S. nullivalvella sp. nov., holotype, BMNH Microlep. slide no. 31013; 38, S. sabahensis sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide no. ZZWGW003." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
): Pleural lobes of eighth segment very broad and strongly sclerotized, lateral margin arched, protruding apically. Brachia of uncus sclerotized, broad at base, spatulate in distal 2/3, slightly expanded distally. Valva broad subtriangular, costa slightly concave at middle, ventral margin curved to right angle, apex bluntly rounded; valvella shuttle-shaped, with several distal setae and a long seta at distal 1/5. Anellus very long, reaching 1/3 length of uncus brachium apically, heavily sclerotized, cone-shaped, curved to blunt angle at distal 1/ 5, acuminate at apex. Phallus very strong, parallel margined, twisted and coiled with many tiny cornuti scattered from distal 1/3 to distal 1/6; main cornutus a longitudinal spicula, running from basal 1/8 to distal 1/4 of phallus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,978,1867]" box="[201,415,1518,1542]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
